<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="d6c351fd-f134-44e4-9690-470bc073c473" >

    <p>Breakout Rooms allow you to split your Zoom meeting into small groups automatically or manually. Breakout rooms mimic in-person small group discussions, seperate from the main meeting. Participants have full audio, video and screen sharing capabilities.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Each breakout room can have a maximum of 200 participants.</li> 
 <li>You can create <strong>up to</strong> 50 separate sessions/breakout rooms. Meetings with 200 participants <strong>may only have 30 </strong>breakout rooms, while meetings with fewer participants may have more.</li> 
 <li>If you already know how you want to split up your participants, you can pre-assign breakout rooms.</li> 
 <li>Breakout rooms can be populated with members of your D2L Brightspace course groups.</li> 
</ul>
    





