   <li><strong>Tip:&nbsp;</strong>Press Ctrl + F (or Command + F on MacOS) and search "Annotations" to quickly find the setting.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ol> 
<p>Note:&nbsp;You must logout of the Zoom Desktop Client and login to it again for this setting to take affect.</p> 
<h4>How to access Annotation tools</h4> 
<p>While viewing a shared screen, click <strong>"View Options"</strong>, then&nbsp;<strong>"Annotate"</strong> at the top.</p>
    





